Q fever, Tunisia
Information received on 16 Mar 2012 from Dr Abdelhak Benyounes, Directeur general des services veterinaires, Direction generale des services veterinaires, Ministere de l'agriculture et de l'environnement, Tunis, Tunisia

Summary
Report type Immediate notification (Final report)
Start date 22 Dec 2011
Date of 1st confirmation of the event 06 Jan 2012
Report date 16 Mar 2012
Date submitted to OIE 16 Mar 2012
Date event resolved 15 Mar 2012
Reason for notification Reoccurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence October 2006
Manifestation of disease Clinical disease
Causal agent Coxiella burnetii
Nature of diagnosis Suspicion, Clinical, Laboratory (basic)
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country

New outbreaks
Outbreak 1 Om elferth, Saiden, Kebili nord, Kebili
Date of start of the outbreak 22 Dec 2011
Outbreak status Resolved (15 Mar 2012)
Epidemiological unit Farm

Species Goats
Susceptible 74
Cases 2
Deaths 0
Destroyed 0
Slaughtered 6

Summary of outbreaks Total outbreaks: 1

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection
Unknown or inconclusive
Vectors

Epidemiological comments It is the same animal population from which samples were taken for Q fever and chlamydiosis (see also immediate notification on 16 March 2012). No new animals have been introduced and no cases have been observed nearby.

Control measures
Measures applied
Control of arthropods
Disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s)
Modified stamping out
Vaccination prohibited
Treatment of affected animals (broad-spectrum antibiotics for the other animals in the farm and suspected to be infected)
Measures to be applied
No other measures

Future Reporting
The event is resolved. No more reports will be submitted

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-Mail
promed@promedmail.org

